<item>
            <title>[LU-4117] sanity-hsm uses $MOUNT on $CLIENT2 for copytool</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4117</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By default (and in autotest) sanity-hsm runs the copytool on $CLIENT2 using $MOUNT. There are several tests in sanity-hsm that also use this mount point (12, 30a, 30b, 57). On a single node run (which nobody cares about but me &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;) the copytool doesn&apos;t have node defined and if you run it on the single node then the CT uses the same mount point as everything. It&apos;s find to run the CT on CLIENT1 or CLIENT2 it should just run on a new and obscure mount point. By obscure I mean not $MOUNT and not $MOUNT2.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
